caption: Awesome atmosphere and super friendly service. The menu was crisp and enchanting. Will definitely recommend this restaurant to my friends. Reasonable prices and generous portions. Great job.
Go to take out place. I always get the Sesame Tofu and Thai Tea. I moved recently and this is the #1 thing I miss about my old place.

Great restaurant!  I've ordered from A1 Asian Fusion for years now.  My family loves the food. We all have favorite dishes that we never get tired of (Steamed Shrimp and broccoli, Singapore Mei fun, California rolls, shrimp shumai just to name few of our go-to items).  Recently we've ordered lots of steamed vegetables that we eat over several meals.  A1 uses really fresh produce so the vegetables are fresh, firm, plentiful and we don't have to cook!  Try them today...you will be happy that you did.
The food here is delicious!! The Ginger dressing on the salad is so fresh, light and very good.
first time ordering from them the fried rice with basil was okay. will need to sample other dishes to give it a true 4 or 5 stars
I'd say the flavors of the food is good, but overall the food is not worth the price you pay.
Our family’s favorite restaurant! Food is ALWAYS GOOD and delivery is FAST!!

I go with my wife to this restaurant from time to time! This is my favorite place to to have a good dinner.  I go there frequently. The food is excellent, the workers are professional and the rates are decent. I like being in this restaurant to have a tasty supper.
A1 Asian Fusion attempted to delivery my order three times because I had forgotten my phone and they couldn’t reach me! Great customer service. Great food!
Love this place! Super delicious, personable, fast…if you order direct from there. Through a delivery app may change your opinion (don’t do it :). They have consistent quality, great place.
Service is extremely clean fast and safe, I have seen this restaurant for years living in Harlem but never anticipated the food to be so good.. I appreciated the meal 5 stars
Great sushi spot. I love their food! Very pleasant and quick.
OUTSTANDING SUSHI

This place is amazing and reasonably priced. We enjoyed our food very much. Customer service is decent and they serve you quickly. My soup was a little too salty and my spring rolls were kinda dry. I will come back if I'm in the area, they have potential for improvement. I do recommend.
Very good and reasonably pruced food and nice customer service.

This place can do much better I expect more from my neighborhood sushi place. So, I'm in the middle of watching a good Russian crime movie I'm on the edge of my seat on my cozy sofa in my cozy Manhattan apartment. I get hungry so I pick up my cell after viewing online menu decide on A1 Asian Fusion. I place order on cell and receive order no more than ten minutes later and what I get is micro sushi and watery tasteless soup.  I don't know why I always order from this place when I'm in the middle of a good Russian crime movie but they always let me down. I have given this place chance after chance to improve  they have not so they have lost a good steady customer. So if they don't care then I don't care to place anymore orders. Udachi

I normally order food with other co workers and today I decided I needed to get out of the office and have lunch t the location. I ordered a Bento Box with chicken and when I asked for hot sauce in place of the soy sauce which I can not have I was told it would cost me more. So because I have some restrictions I have to pay more. I told the lady to forget it. She turned around and walked away. I came back to my office and informed the co workers that we should never be ordering from them again. Your food is good but customer service is lacking and nickle and diming the customer is really poor practice.
The food is always good and is fresh. I recieve excellent customer service!

We ordered: A1 Asian Fusion - fried salmon rolls - highlight! - octopus - so so tender like the A1 Asian Fusion style pulpo with A1 Asian Fusion bravas - salmon in broth - perfectly tender and flaky - grilled sea bass - still tastes like the sea - dark chocolate bread pudding - rich and not too sweat, coffee ice cream was delightfully bitter - mango tapioca pudding - milky and sweet

Food was good but for an empty restaurant and me being the ONLY customer,how do you forget to put in part of my order?!?! The server just casually said, “oh I forgot to put your dumplings in” and this wasn’t until I was done eating my rolls. Very lazy of her. There were no customers! I should have gotten my dumplings !!!
Great service as usual. I love the rośe, its called Babe. Very intimate.😊
I've been ordering from here for a while love the food and  I Just noticed check out has  tax and fees added to order on top of the delivery charge.   Beware.

Perfect

Just walked in and tried to sit down and eat at 10:30 PM... even though they close at 11:30 they told me and my partner that “We are only open for take out and delivery”. They had a massive brightly lit sign outside that said open, no chairs were stacked & NO ONE was cleaning. I should add, were two black women sounds like they didn’t want to serve us because this doesn’t make any sense.
The customer service is constantly prompt, lovely vibes, welcoming staff members. Will return again when I get here.
Yummy
This place simply knows how to please their clients. Consistently with a very friendly approach. The food is affordably priced, regularly fresh and clean.
This place has really good food, the drunken noodles are my absolute favorite.
Great food and professional service. You can get either fresh Sushi or traditional Chinese takeout here. Can't go wrong either way.
Not a fan. The wings are great and sushi is ok. The rest of the food always taste like something is missing.

Such good dinner memories here. everything is good even the music !! music is a bonus. super friendly. loud but .. it's fun !! popular dishes run out sometimes try to beat the crowds before 6. my mouth is watering just thinking about the ribs. pricy tho.
Great moshi. My first time trying it. Love it

Came here with my african american mother and friend..  our waitress seemed very awful in what i can only interpret to be racially tinged... it was insane... we were cut off when ordering sassed with every sentence...  it felt like we were an inconvenience to serve from the second we walked in the door.. i did my best to buffer how terrible she was to us (as a former waitress) just to enjoy the meal and i gave a tip just because i felt not giving one would make her feel indignant in her terrible treatment of us (especially since i do believe it was racial)... my mom is vegetarian and she was trying to figure out something to eat (the waitress was not helpful at all)  and she was like okay I’ll eat this even though it’s technically not vegetarian just so my daughter can enjoy herself today... and literally the waitress goes oh so you’re not vegetarian then (to be condescending) she was so disrespectful to my mom the whole dinner... i was horrified.. would not recommend.. and just a petty side note they didn’t  have peanut sauce..

The service takes forever. My food was ready and the waitress didn't get it for about 15 minutes. Not to mention I waited about the same amount of time just for the lady to bring me my miso soup. Then the lady kept suggesting that I get meat when I specifically told her I was vegetarian. After my meal was over I went to pay and was 20 cents off for the minimum for card. When I asked for them to charge me the extra 20 cents they said no, but gladly charged me for a soda I didn't drink. All the while the waitress is saying "why don't you have cash".  OH and she couldn't remember what I ordered so she came to me twice to ask my order again.

The Papaya salad is low on accompaniments but HIGH in FLAVOR. There were peanuts, tomato and a few hidden green beans. The dressing was incredible and the papaya was nice and crisp. My curry pancake was nothing like I've ever tasted. I would go back just to order that. The service was also welcoming. I will definitely be back, I'm thankful for the recommendation.
Food is really good. Love there carb rangoon but do wish it came with more than 3 pieces. It's small but very clean and they have a 4pm-8pm happy hour Monday-Friday.
very good

Food is very good and they have a solid variety in their menu. I've ordered here over 10 times and really enjoy their sushi rolls and Thai dishes.  Most of the negative reviews here and on other services are for their delivery and service. I have yet to have any bad experience.  In general, I wouldn't recommend ordering "sashimi" unless you are going to sit down and pay $40 per person at a more focused restaurant.  Highly recommend for casual delivery dining !

I would not recommend eating here. The food is of average quality and the customer service is trash. I ordered a lunch special today on seamless and they cancelled my order because  It didn’t meet the $10 minimum before tip. Mind you it was only $9.50 before tip and I tipped 20% via the app but okay I could understand if they called and asked me to add to the order. Instead they just called to tell me they cancelled my order and hung up.
Aa Harlem continues to grow and change, this place will be more of a neighborhood favorite.
Not a fan of fusion restaurants but the sushi is convenient! Spicy tuna and eel sauce are favorites. Love to order the roti canai and bok choy takeaway.
Yummy,.small plates , nice ambience, decent prices

Food was delivered later than anticipated schedule.  Arrived cold so fried veggie dumplings tasted horrible.  Also ordered Sushi and I have had better from a grocery store. First and Last time ordering
Very good sushi  :)
Hi this is Miriam from the Brooklyn Agency saying Hi. It is a real pleasure working with you guys.

Love this place !! recommended by a friend and she was right! Ordered the unagi as appetizer. It's so fresh and the sauce is perfect.  I also love their miso sea bass! Its so soft it melts in your mouth. It's a must try (I can finish two of those. ) Pork chop is also very good and it comes with fried taro chips for both dishes. Con- quite small inside and no valet parking

A great restaurant serving everything from Indian to Chinese to Japanese to Thai.  I ordered an indian nan bread.  Very good!  It was served with peanut sauce and shrimp chips.  I also ordered a chinese sauteed baby bok choy dish.  Very good! The sahimi was delicious!  The udon soup was good as well!
Lunch, $9 for a bento shrimp teriyaki is ok. But server/casher attitude is very unwelcoming, almost impolite. Pad Thai is the worst that I've ever had. Miso soup is as expected.
We had an excellent time and the food was amazing.
I have ordered only lunch while at work in Harlem. I LOVE IT!!
The Best
Asian + Sushi Food
The best duck fried rice I’ve ever tasted!! Salmon habaci was amazing as well!!! Come here
I’ve never been to this establishment however I always order delivery.  The food has always been received at a reasonable time within ordering and not to mention delish!

Really average and below average food. Nice and cosy inside but food was unfortunately not great. Had Basil Shrimp, Satay Chicken and Eel Sushi. Considered finding another restaurant to eat at after Chicken Satay was disappointing but thought we would give the restaurant an opportunity for redemption. Unfortunately there was no improvement from there. Basil Shrimp was average and Eel Sushi was not great. Prices are fairly expensive considering the quality. Definitely will not be going back. No redeeming factors.
Food is pretty good. Is a nice place to eat Asian food. You can also order on the Internet.
Decent food, not to expensive and usually very fast
If you like your Thai food very spicy and flavorful, this might not be the place for you.

The food was okay, I would give that 3 .5 stars. The service was good up until it was time to leave. I gave a 10% tip and the waitress did not seem to have an issue with it. Another woman working there came over to the table and asked if the service was okay. I said it was fine, no complaints. So she asked why such a low tip. I was completely shocked. How unprofessional is that. I get it, some people really need their tips but tips are a generous gift not a necessity. Furthermore, I literally gave all I had to offer. I was baffled. After explaining to her that was all I have to offer she threw the check book down, with the tip in it for me to take back. Won't ever come here again.

It's very crazy that I had to pay for  SAUCE here at A1 Asian Fusion! The customer service is disgusting. The restaurant's owner thinks he is still in Thailand. I have been eating Thai food for almost 3 years in NYC, but I never had to pay for spicy sauce!

Haven't eaten here yet, but the place looked quiet and very clean, I took the photo because I will be going here in the next few days, neighborhood is up and coming I love what's being done with Harlem.
Lovely intimate atmosphere w delicious food. Reasonable prices, lovely presentation and excellent service
Very nice venue polite service every time i buy dinner here.  ..
Great food, inexpensive, nice staff and ambience.
Always the best! Where take out or eat in... food hood and fresh. Service impeccable!! The best in Harlem!!
First time ordering from here... Great Customer service, we had Chicken Teriyaki it was amazing w salad very fresh love this place my new favorite💖
I'd rate a zero if I could. I got food poisoning after eating delivery sushi from this restaurant.  Avoid at all costs.
Great service. Great food. Great atmosphere.
Excellent takeout! Super fast, order is always correct, and wide variety of high quality. I recommend the green curry and the sushi.
Great food great customer service!! Christine is awesome
Good sushi lunch special.

My new go to for asian cuisine in harlem. Love the food and appreciate the customer service. Thai wings, general tso's, salmon teriyaki, all great choices I've tried. Had a mix up with the order once. They handled it immediately and made me a repeat customer. A1 from Day1!
Sushi and all fish I've tried great. Love hibachi combo meal. Have not been disappointed. Had to call them and thank them for the great deliveries! :)

I ordered a Saturday afternoon at 1:16pm and called the resturant twice. Apparently they have a delivery problem. Now it's 2:54pm and still waiting. I think the least they can do is call me to reschedule a delivery and a compensation. (More than 1h30min of wait !).  Ordered several times in the past and never had any problem. Sadly this time we have one.
Ordered delivery at 144th and Broadway. I was skeptical about someplace "far away", but I thought that there were plenty of options, delivery was fast, food was good, and service was excellent

Excellent place, so confy and staff is great. Best sushi place in the area, prices are good and they have a really good sort of combination and platters. Just once I try Thai Food and it was really good.
